cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.COM 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses full-duplex communication in cellular networks, which is a networking topic. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a mathematical framework based on stochastic geometry to maximize the harvested rate gains in 3-node topology. This involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the design paradigm via pulse-shaping and partial overlap between UL and DL channels to maximize the harvested rate gains in 3NT, which involves control systems concepts. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance of different duplexing schemes in cellular networks, which is relevant to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.COM (Computers and Society) - This category is less likely, but the paper may have implications for the societal impact of cellular networks and their efficiency.
